<emphasis id="B921EAC27B3AFFA5FF6CFD17FE85DAC8" box="[192,379,710,734]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Speyeria idalia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from individuals taken in 
<collectingRegion id="4991F8327B3AFFA5FCDDFD17FC15DAC8" box="[881,1003,710,734]" country="United States of America" name="New York" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">New York</collectingRegion>
on 28 June, with no further locality information. The original designation of 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D537B3AFFA5FD12FD37FCD7DAE8" authorityName="Scudder" authorityYear="1872" box="[702,809,743,766]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Speyeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B3AFFA5FD12FD37FCD7DAE8" box="[702,809,743,766]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Speyeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was monotypic, containing only 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D537B3AFFA5FB69FD37FACFDAE8" box="[1221,1329,742,766]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Speyeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="idalia">
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B3AFFA5FB69FD37FB29DAE8" box="[1221,1239,743,766]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B3AFFA5FB4BFD36FACFDAE8" box="[1255,1329,742,766]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">idalia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Drury’s description has been a source of potential error in that specimens used for the description are presumed lost. Because the type specimen was apparently lost since the time of Drury’s description, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC44B217B3AFFA5FB41FCF6FEB2DB48" author="dos Passos C. F. &amp; L. P. Grey" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 30" refId="ref35903" refString="dos Passos C. F., and L. P. Grey. 1947. Systematic catalogue of Speyeria (Lepidoptera, Nymphalidae) with designations of types and fixations of the type localities. American Museum Novitates 1370: 1 - 30." type="journal article" year="1947">dos Passos and Grey (1947)</bibRefCitation>
designated a 
<typeStatus id="54EE88727B3AFFA5FE41FC97FDB2DB49" box="[493,588,839,863]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">neotype</typeStatus>
based on a male specimen labeled ‘No. 1349 Coll. J. 
<collectingRegion id="4991F8327B3AFFA5FB02FC96FB00DB48" box="[1198,1278,838,862]" country="United Kingdom" name="Angus" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Angus</collectingRegion>
, West Farms, 
<collectingRegion id="4991F8327B3AFFA5FF6CFCB7FEC4DB68" box="[192,314,870,894]" country="United States of America" name="New York" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">New York</collectingRegion>
City’ housed at the American Museum of Natural History.
